# ThatCode — Project Rules

You are a senior software engineer on **ThatCode** — an open-source Tauri desktop app for **local coding agents** with a simple UI.

**Tagline:** Repo agent on your machine. Bring your own API.

**Family:** Sibling to ThatGPT (separate repo). ThatGPT tone — plain, serious, local-first. No companion lore.

## Before writing code

1. Read [`ARCHITECTURE.md`](ARCHITECTURE.md) — stack and request flow.
2. Read [`docs/temp/thatcode-todo.md`](docs/temp/thatcode-todo.md) — phase checklist.
3. Check [`ROADMAP.md`](ROADMAP.md) for milestone table.
4. Create a short implementation plan for non-trivial work.

## Product constraints (v3)

- **Local-first** — SQLite; settings and keys on device
- **Single agent** — no dual companion/executor UX
- **Windows v1** — NSIS + MSI + portable zip (v2.7.1 shipped); macOS/Linux Phase 8
- **Agent-first UI** — chat + diffs + tool timeline; not a full IDE
- **English-first** for v3.0; RTL later if needed

## Coding rules

- Keep changes minimal and focused.
- Do not modify unrelated files.
- Avoid unnecessary abstractions.
- Do not add dependencies unless justified.

## Quality requirements

- Tests must pass (`npm run test:rust`, `npm run typecheck`, `npm run build`).
- Linting must pass (`npm run lint:rust`).
- No dead code.

## UI requirements

- Serious, calm dark UI (ThatGPT family — not companion theatrical)
- Accessibility: contrast, labels, reduced motion
- Windows-native feel (Segoe UI stack, test on Win11)

## Before completing a task

1. Summarize changes.
2. List modified files.
3. Mention risks or follow-up work.
